title: node limit
pid: 9130ccd0-f0e0-403c-baeb-cbd136dc2bd7
body: |2-
  If each node knows how to update itself,
  traversal order becomes less important.

  Never delete from what's in a view already.
  Regardless of traversal order, upon hitting the nodelimit,
  truncate what remains to be drawn 
  to some minimal but complete structure.
  I suspect that just means removing all remaining definitive view requests
  from indefinitive nodes and then completing everything.
